ATTACHMENT A
Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Whitetail Solar 3, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
WHITETAIL SOLAR 13 LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Whitetail Solar 3, LLC ("Whitetail 3") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Whitetail 3 generating facility ("Whitetail 3 Facility").
The Whitetail 3 Facility is a solar generating facility located in Franklin County, Pennsylvania. The Whitetail 3 Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Mid-Atlantic Interstate Transmission, LLC and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Whitetail 3's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Whitetail 3 Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Whitetail 3's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Whitetail 3 shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $236,426.28. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $19,702.19.
